# Architecture document — read and maintain

[`ARCHITECTURE.md`](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) is the canonical map of Passport. Agents must treat it as source of truth alongside the code.

## Before starting work

1. **Read** `ARCHITECTURE.md` and [`docs/domain-specification.md`](../../docs/domain-specification.md) (Ubiquitous Language).
2. Skim existing code in the same package.

## Before marking a task done

Update `ARCHITECTURE.md` when you changed routes, tables, packages, auth, or JWT claims.  
Update `docs/domain-specification.md` when domain language or invariants change ([domain-model.mdc](domain-model.mdc)).

## Never

- Add significant behavior without reading ARCHITECTURE.md and the domain spec first.
- Leave either document stale after a structural or domain change.
